.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Badge \- NIP\-58 Badges
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Badge;
\&
\&    # Define a badge (kind 30009, addressable)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Badge\->definition(
\&        pubkey      => $issuer_pubkey,
\&        identifier  => \*(Aqbravery\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqMedal of Bravery\*(Aq,
\&        description => \*(AqAwarded to users demonstrating bravery\*(Aq,
\&        image       => [\*(Aqhttps://nostr.academy/awards/bravery.png\*(Aq, \*(Aq1024x1024\*(Aq],
\&        thumbs      => [
\&            [\*(Aqhttps://nostr.academy/awards/bravery_256x256.png\*(Aq, \*(Aq256x256\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Award a badge (kind 8)
\&    my $award = Net::Nostr::Badge\->award(
\&        pubkey   => $issuer_pubkey,
\&        badge    => \*(Aq30009:issuer_pk:bravery\*(Aq,
\&        awardees => [[$recipient_pk, \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq]],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Display badges on profile (kind 10008, replaceable)
\&    my $profile = Net::Nostr::Badge\->profile_badges(
\&        pubkey => $user_pubkey,
\&        badges => [
\&            { definition => \*(Aq30009:issuer:bravery\*(Aq, award => $award_event_id },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Categorize badges into a set (kind 30008, addressable)
\&    my $set = Net::Nostr::Badge\->badge_set(
\&        pubkey     => $user_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-favorites\*(Aq,
\&        badges     => [
\&            { definition => \*(Aq30009:issuer:bravery\*(Aq, award => $award_event_id },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any badge event
\&    my $badge = Net::Nostr::Badge\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Badge\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-58 (Badges). Four event kinds are used to define, award,
display, and categorize badges:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBBadge Definition\fR (kind 30009) \- Addressable event defining a badge.
Published by the badge issuer. Can be updated.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBBadge Award\fR (kind 8) \- Awards a badge to one or more pubkeys.
Immutable and non\-transferable.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBProfile Badges\fR (kind 10008) \- Replaceable event listing badges
a user has accepted, in display order.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBBadge Set\fR (kind 30008) \- Addressable event categorizing accepted
badges into labeled groups.
.PP
Badge image recommended aspect ratio is 1:1 with a high\-res size of
1024x1024 pixels. Recommended thumbnail dimensions are 512x512 (xl),
256x256 (l), 64x64 (m), 32x32 (s), and 16x16 (xs).
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $badge = Net::Nostr::Badge\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Badge\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event". Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS definition
.IX Subsection "definition"
.Vb 9
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Badge\->definition(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,             # required
\&        identifier  => \*(Aqbravery\*(Aq,               # required (d tag)
\&        name        => \*(AqMedal of Bravery\*(Aq,      # optional (MAY)
\&        description => \*(AqAwarded to brave users\*(Aq, # optional (MAY)
\&        image       => [\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq1024x1024\*(Aq],    # optional (MAY, dims optional)
\&        thumbs      => [[\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq256x256\*(Aq]],    # optional (MAY, dims optional)
\&        created_at  => time(),                  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30009 badge definition Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR
is required and becomes the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. All other fields are optional per
the spec.
.SS award
.IX Subsection "award"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Badge\->award(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,                       # required
\&        badge    => \*(Aq30009:issuer_pk:bravery\*(Aq,         # required (a tag)
\&        awardees => [[$pk, \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq], [$pk2]],   # required (p tags)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 8 badge award Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`badge\*(C'\fR is the
coordinate of a kind 30009 badge definition. \f(CW\*(C`awardees\*(C'\fR is an arrayref
of arrayrefs, each containing a pubkey and optional relay URL. At least
one awardee is required.
.SS profile_badges
.IX Subsection "profile_badges"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Badge\->profile_badges(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,                     # required
\&        badges     => [                                # required
\&            { definition => \*(Aq30009:pk:id\*(Aq, award => $eid, award_relay => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        badge_sets => [\*(Aq30008:pk:set\-name\*(Aq],           # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 10008 profile badges Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`badges\*(C'\fR is an
arrayref of hashrefs, each with \f(CW\*(C`definition\*(C'\fR (badge coordinate),
\&\f(CW\*(C`award\*(C'\fR (award event id), and optional \f(CW\*(C`award_relay\*(C'\fR. Tags are emitted
as consecutive \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR pairs in order. \f(CW\*(C`badge_sets\*(C'\fR optionally
references kind 30008 badge set coordinates.
.SS badge_set
.IX Subsection "badge_set"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Badge\->badge_set(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,                     # required
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-favorites\*(Aq,                  # required (d tag)
\&        badges     => [                                # required
\&            { definition => \*(Aq30009:pk:id\*(Aq, award => $eid },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30008 badge set Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR is
required and becomes the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. \f(CW\*(C`badges\*(C'\fR uses the same format as
"profile_badges".
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $badge = Net::Nostr::Badge\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a badge event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Badge\*(C'\fR object. Recognizes kinds
30009, 8, 10008, and 30008. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
.PP
For kind 30009 (definition): \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`thumbs\*(C'\fR.
.PP
For kind 8 (award): \f(CW\*(C`badge\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`awardees\*(C'\fR.
.PP
For kind 10008 (profile badges): \f(CW\*(C`badges\*(C'\fR.
.PP
For kind 30008 (badge set): \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`badges\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Deprecated kind 30008 events with \f(CW\*(C`d=profile_badges\*(C'\fR are treated as
equivalent to kind 10008.
.PP
Profile badges and badge sets expect consecutive \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag pairs.
Unpaired \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags (without a following \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR) and unpaired \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags
(without a preceding \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR) are ignored, per the spec recommendation.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Badge\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-58 badge event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 30009, 8, 10008, or 30008
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30009 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 8 missing \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag referencing a kind 30009 definition, or missing \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30008 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value (badge definitions and badge sets).
.SS name
.IX Subsection "name"
The badge name (from \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
The badge description (from \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS image
.IX Subsection "image"
Arrayref of the image URL and optional dimensions (e.g.
\&\f(CW\*(C`[\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq1024x1024\*(Aq]\*(C'\fR), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS thumbs
.IX Subsection "thumbs"
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a thumbnail URL and optional
dimensions. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS badge
.IX Subsection "badge"
The badge definition coordinate (from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag in award events).
.SS awardees
.IX Subsection "awardees"
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a pubkey and optional relay URL.
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS badges
.IX Subsection "badges"
Arrayref of hashrefs for profile badges and badge sets. Each entry has
\&\f(CW\*(C`definition\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`award\*(C'\fR, and optional \f(CW\*(C`award_relay\*(C'\fR. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS badge_sets
.IX Subsection "badge_sets"
Arrayref of badge set coordinates (from profile badges events).
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-58 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/58.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
